        "heading_url": "",
        "heading_color": "#002855",
        "text": "<p><strong>New Zealand’s global reputation for premium wine comes from its temperate maritime climate, free-draining soils, and long growing season.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Warm days and cool nights enhance ripening while preserving natural acidity</li>\n<li>Alluvial and gravelly soils offer excellent drainage and root penetration</li>\n<li>A long harvest window encourages full flavour and varietal expression</li>\n</ul>\nThese conditions help us produce wines with vibrant aromatics, purity of fruit, and distinctive regional character.",
